    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Christ’s life with mine now one and the same is."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Union, communion, fellowship sweet,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I lay my hand on His head most beauteous;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "All of His virtues flow into me."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Chorus 2:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Wholly accepted! Turned into ashes!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Released from self, my old man has died!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Burn me, reduce me, till I am nothing;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Hail resurrection; hail the sunrise!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "chorus"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Manger to cross, the life of the God-man,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "His story now my story will be."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Could I myself say yes to be slaughtered?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Never! yet through Him, “Yes, willingly!”"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What He experienced, I would experience;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What He passed through, I enter into."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Loving and tender, to Him surrender,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Two parties meld, one living pursue."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Fire not of wrath nor judgment nor terror,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "‘Twas love I met there, warmed on the hearth."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I could approach Him, and He embraced me,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Fully received me, filled me with mirth."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "All through the dark night, tend to the fire;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "O Lord, our love rekindle anew."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That, life to life, a savor far-reaching,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We’d conquer captives, add men to You."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Worldlings despise us, count us as nothing,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet to our God we’re precious indeed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Highly regarded, ashes to gemstones,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Treasure-built city’s our destiny!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    }
  ],
